50|$|In September 2010 Hanni {{launched}} a new political party called the British Columbia Heritage Party. The new party advocated creating a provincial constitution, replacing the existing first-past-the-post voting system with preferential voting, and replacing taxation system with a <b>single</b> rate income <b>tax</b> or a <b>single</b> rate consumption <b>tax</b> (decided in a referendum).|$|R
